- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the definition and properties of operators on terms, such as substitution and freshness, which are relevant to programming languages. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper mentions support for semantic interpretation and interaction with standard operators, which are important aspects of software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper deals with the formalization of a theory of syntax, which is a topic within formal languages and automata theory. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper's focus on syntax and semantic interpretation may also be relevant to the computation and language sub-category.
